    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-07-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="452" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d452">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 452.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Buck</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-07-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 30,
                            1885</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to instruction No. 129, of May 29th
                        last, I have to ask that you will report in the case of Owen Young, the
                        American citizen, whose assassin, notwithstanding the vigorous action of the
                        late minister at Lima, had not at last accounts been arrested. Meantime you
                        will please refer to the correspondence in the case and press the subject of
                        the assassin’s arrest. * * *</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
